<paragraph blockId="137.[151,1437,1083,1302]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis box="[207,450,1162,1186]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
: The male imago can be separated from other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Edwards" authorityYear="1937" box="[1148,1250,1162,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Smittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxoniana">
<emphasis box="[1148,1250,1162,1185]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">oxoniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup by the long, apically parallel-sided anal point and the low hind leg ratio of 0.44.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="137.[151,1437,1083,1302]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis box="[207,323,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Etymology</emphasis>
: Named in honor of Kaare Aagaard, Norwegian Institute of Nature Research, Trondheim, 
<collectingCountry box="[1302,1393,1240,1264]" name="Norway" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Norway</collectingCountry>
, the collector of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="137.[151,1437,1356,1541]" box="[151,363,1356,1381]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Male imago</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="137.[151,1437,1356,1541]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
All measurements and ratios within the variation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Ferrington Jr &amp; Saether" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[711,827,1396,1419]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Hydrosmittia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruttneri">
<emphasis box="[711,827,1396,1419]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">H. ruttneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following exceptions: Total length/wing length 1.55. Costal extension (
<figureCitation box="[414,524,1434,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 50" captionStartId="138.[151,250,1805,1828]" captionTargetBox="[305,1294,206,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-47@138.[216,1350,192,1780]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 50. Hydrosmittia aagaardi sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288427/files/figure.png" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Fig. 50 A</figureCitation>
) 46 µm long, with false vein extending from base of costal extension to 199 µm. Front leg with ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[332,340,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">3</subScript>
126 µm long, ta 
<subScript attach="left" box="[521,529,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">4</subScript>
81 µm long, LR 
<subScript attach="left" box="[712,720,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">3</subScript>
0.44, SV 
<subScript attach="left" box="[823,831,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">3</subScript>
4.42, 
<collectingRegion box="[899,935,1474,1497]" country="Turkey" name="Bolu" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">BR</collectingRegion>
<subScript attach="left" box="[936,944,1488,1502]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">2</subScript>
3.9. Anal point (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1232,1473,1497]" captionStart="FIGURE 50" captionStartId="138.[151,250,1805,1828]" captionTargetBox="[305,1294,206,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-47@138.[216,1350,192,1780]" captionTargetPageId="138" captionText="FIGURE 50. Hydrosmittia aagaardi sp. n., male. A—wing; B—head; C—third palpomere; D—cibarial pump and stipes; E— virga; F—hypopygium, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5288427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5288427/files/figure.png" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Fig. 50 F</figureCitation>
) 46 µm long, with weak scattered microtrichia to apex. Gonostylus with weak heel.
</paragraph>
